National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and South African National Security Advisor Sydney Mufamadi had a conversation where they reaffirmed the commitment of Presidents Biden and Ramaphosa to strengthen the bilateral relationship between the U.S. and South Africa. Sullivan pledged support to South Africa in response to the recent deadly floods in Kwa Zulu Natal. He also emphasized the United States' willingness to work closely with South Africa on various issues, including the crisis in Ukraine, trade and investment, health systems and security, climate change, counterterrorism, and regional security efforts. Both advisors expressed the need for an immediate end to Russia's aggression in Ukraine and discussed the impact on supply chains, commodity prices, and food security in Africa.